Science is not just about reading and memorising; it’s about doing!  Throughout this textbook, you’ll find \textbf{Investigations}. These are hands-on activities, experiments, and projects designed to help you actively explore scientific concepts and develop your scientific skills.

\textbf{Investigations are designed to:}

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Apply your knowledge in practical contexts:}  Investigations give you the chance to put what you’ve learned into practice and see science in action.
    \item \textbf{Develop your experimental skills:}  You'll learn how to design experiments, collect data, analyse results, and draw conclusions – all essential skills for a scientist.
    \item \textbf{Encourage collaboration and teamwork:} Many investigations are designed to be done in groups, fostering teamwork and communication skills.
    \item \textbf{Make learning more engaging and memorable:}  Hands-on activities make learning more interactive and fun, helping you remember concepts more effectively.
    \item \textbf{Reflect real scientific practices:}  Investigations mirror how scientists actually work, giving you a taste of real scientific inquiry.
\end{itemize}

Each investigation will typically include:

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{An introduction and purpose:}  Explaining what you’ll be investigating and why it’s important.
    \item \textbf{A list of materials needed:}  Making sure you have everything ready before you start.
    \item \textbf{Step-by-step instructions:}  Clear and easy-to-follow directions to guide you through the investigation.
    \item \textbf{Questions for analysis and discussion:}  Helping you reflect on your results and deepen your understanding.
\end{itemize}

We strongly encourage you to actively participate in all investigations.  They are a crucial part of learning science and will help you develop a deeper and more practical understanding of the subject. Remember to always follow safety guidelines and ask for help if you're unsure about anything!

