At the end of each chapter, you'll find a \textbf{Summary}. This is a concise overview of the key concepts and learning points covered in the chapter.  Summaries are excellent tools for revision and for quickly refreshing your memory.

\textbf{Chapter summaries are useful for:}

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Reviewing the main topics:}  They provide a quick recap of the most important information.
    \item \textbf{Identifying key concepts:}  Summaries highlight the core ideas you should take away from each chapter.
    \item \textbf{Preparing for assessments:}  Reading through the summary before a test or quiz is a great way to quickly refresh your knowledge.
    \item \textbf{Checking your understanding:}  If you can understand the summary, it's a good sign you've grasped the main points of the chapter.
    \item \textbf{Organising your notes:}  Summaries can help you structure your own study notes and identify the most crucial information to focus on.
\end{itemize}

Read the chapter summary after you've completed each chapter and again when you are revising. It's a powerful tool for consolidating your learning.

