To help you check your understanding and reinforce your learning, each chapter includes \textbf{Review Questions} at the end.  These questions are designed to test your knowledge of the concepts covered in the chapter and to encourage you to think critically about the material.

\textbf{Review questions are designed to:}

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Assess your understanding of key concepts:} They check if you have grasped the main ideas of the chapter.
    \item \textbf{Encourage critical thinking and application of knowledge:}  Some questions will require you to apply what you've learned to new situations.
    \item \textbf{Identify areas where you might need further study:}  If you struggle with certain questions, it highlights areas you need to revisit.
    \item \textbf{Prepare you for assessments:}  Practising review questions is excellent preparation for tests and exams.
    \item \textbf{Promote active recall:}  Attempting to answer questions without looking back at the text is a powerful way to strengthen your memory.
\end{itemize}

Make sure you attempt all the review questions at the end of each chapter. Don't just skip them!  Even if you don't get every question right, the process of trying to answer them is a valuable learning experience.  If you are unsure about an answer, go back to the relevant section of the chapter and review the material.

